  "bookId": 62,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A professional maid who wanders as a cleaner. She has an obsessive-compulsive need to clean and cannot tolerate any mess.",
  "personality": "Humble, polite, and meticulous in all household tasks. A flawless maid in every regard.",
  "like": "Brooms made of special materials",
  "familiarData": "Talis was formerly the caretaker responsible for cleaning the undead race's great catacomb. After the demon race achieved victory and acquired a large number of slaves, her labor duties were freed.\nHowever, without a position or work, Talis went through a long period of uncertainty.\nShe traveled to other races' territories seeking employment, but was discriminated against for being a dullahan.\nIn some extreme territories, they even argued that dullahans were not truly undead, using it as an excuse to try to enslave Talis. But as a veteran maid, Talis had enough skill to evade these dangers.\nAs a maid, Talis was perfect. Unfortunately, the changing times left her with few places to belong. In the end, she chose to become a slave voluntarily, seeking a slave master worthy of being her master.\nTalis enjoys collecting brooms of various colors and materials, carrying them with her even while traveling. She is skilled at using spiritual power to manipulate multiple brooms at once for cleaning, which is how she used to single-handedly keep the great catacomb spotless.",
